  "datePublished": "2026-03-08",
  "description": "TCCC decision-making becomes most explicit when the number of casualties exceeds the available hands, time, or evacuation capacity.\nTwo related but distinct questions appear:\nTriage: who gets treated first (and at what level of intensity)? Evacuation precedence: who gets moved first when transport is limited? These can align, but they do not have to. A casualty may be medically urgent but logistically impossible to move; another may be movable and time-sensitive.\n",
  "keywords": "military-medicine, trauma, emergency-medicine",
